    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A permanent, deep red pigment containing cadmium. Earliest pigments were composed of pure cadmium sulfoselenide, first patented in Germany in 1892. Variations in the proportions of the cadmium and selenide produce as range of colors from orange to dark maroon. By 1926, cadmium reds were being co-precipitated with barium sulfate to form less expensive cadmium lithopone pigments.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種含鎘的永久性深紅色顏料。最早的鎘紅顏料以純硒硫化鎘製成，西元1892年首度在德國獲頒專利。不同比例的鎘和硒會形成不同的色澤，範圍從橘色到暗褐紅。1926年時以鎘紅與硫酸鋇共同沉澱，形成價格較低之鎘鋅顏料。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
